    <item>
      <title>Shoji Room Divider</title>
      <link>https://kosomon.github.io/project/shojiscreen/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://kosomon.github.io/project/shojiscreen/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When the pandemic lockdown started in Finland, I was stuck working from my apartment. I didn&amp;rsquo;t have a dedicated office, so I decided to build a room divider to wall off a section of my living room. I had long been fascinated by traditional Japanese joinery and architecture which meant that a shoji inspired divider  was the natural choice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The wood is red alder with a beautifully warm color, with Washi paper as a light diffusor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-light-and-shadows-interact-with-the-washi-paper-in-gorgeous-ways&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Sunlight shining through the Washi paper&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/shojiscreen/light_diffusing_hubc6be06da1b3f2952cf38bbfd1ffd4f3_1591230_3866a99a8686824fa568e6347aee4ddd.jpg 400w,
               /project/shojiscreen/light_diffusing_hubc6be06da1b3f2952cf38bbfd1ffd4f3_1591230_b9eae71390b04c07be220bf64e794432.jpg 760w,
               /project/shojiscreen/light_diffusing_hubc6be06da1b3f2952cf38bbfd1ffd4f3_1591230_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://kosomon.github.io/project/shojiscreen/light_diffusing_hubc6be06da1b3f2952cf38bbfd1ffd4f3_1591230_3866a99a8686824fa568e6347aee4ddd.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Light and shadows interact with the Washi paper in gorgeous ways.
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-the-rails-are-joined-to-the-stiles-using-mortice-and-tenon-joints&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Joinery close-up&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/shojiscreen/chamfers_hubbbf426bd51d83e1e754e63abf01bc40_1569230_2da488615fe2a3251d316dd8131dda51.jpg 400w,
               /project/shojiscreen/chamfers_hubbbf426bd51d83e1e754e63abf01bc40_1569230_24b9ed322440a79b974e6a34a4e1f358.jpg 760w,
               /project/shojiscreen/chamfers_hubbbf426bd51d83e1e754e63abf01bc40_1569230_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://kosomon.github.io/project/shojiscreen/chamfers_hubbbf426bd51d83e1e754e63abf01bc40_1569230_2da488615fe2a3251d316dd8131dda51.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      The rails are joined to the stiles using mortice and tenon joints.
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>TV Stand</title>
      <link>https://kosomon.github.io/project/tv-stand/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://kosomon.github.io/project/tv-stand/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;TV stand I built out of oak and painted plywood, using mostly hand tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-the-oak-is-finished-with-danish-oil-which-gives-it-a-beautiful-natural-satin-finish&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Close-up of the oak grain.&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/tv-stand/tv_stand_grain_hu59daef08a1a584f066da5ec404db061a_1662559_4e367c534b4cc38656e9694153628fad.jpg 400w,
               /project/tv-stand/tv_stand_grain_hu59daef08a1a584f066da5ec404db061a_1662559_dcd93208fa60f593d6b2d449fceb119d.jpg 760w,
               /project/tv-stand/tv_stand_grain_hu59daef08a1a584f066da5ec404db061a_1662559_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://kosomon.github.io/project/tv-stand/tv_stand_grain_hu59daef08a1a584f066da5ec404db061a_1662559_4e367c534b4cc38656e9694153628fad.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      The oak is finished with Danish Oil, which gives it a beautiful natural satin finish.
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
